#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""hpc-alloc: allocate Yale YCRC compute nodes (Bouchet et al.) for remote development.

Mechanism: submits a sleeper batch job via sbatch (works on ANY partition, unlike
salloc which only works on the devel partitions of public clusters), waits for it
to start, then writes an SSH alias that ProxyJumps through the login node to the
compute node. Both hops are multiplexed with ControlMaster, so Duo MFA happens
once per ControlPersist window and repeated commands are near-instant.

Connection drops (VPN loss, laptop sleep) are detected by probing, healed by
resetting stale masters, and never mistaken for job death. Exit code 3 means
"connection lost, needs an interactive `hpc-alloc connect` to re-auth".

GPU etiquette: YCRC cancels jobs whose GPUs sit idle (warning at 30 min). Direct
GPU allocations therefore self-release after --idle-timeout minutes of GPU
idleness (default 30, matching the warning threshold), and `hpc-alloc run`
executes commands as short-lived batch jobs so GPUs are only held while
actually computing.

Requires only a VPN connection and a NetID with an uploaded SSH key
(https://sshkeys.ycrc.yale.edu/). Run `hpc-alloc setup` first.
"""

